\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Select the Clef Tool.  Click on a staff to place the clef where the pointer is.  The selection area of a clef is any location within the bounding box of the clef.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b Clef placement\b0  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 As for any staff object, clefs are automatically placed when the system is adjusted (see \b Adjustment\b0 ).  To otherwise move a clef,  select the clef and hold the mouse button down to drag the clef to a desired location.  The  clef attaches itself to the nearest staff.  To change the staff line associated with the keycenter of the clef, Alt-drag the clef or use the Clef Inspector.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa80\li0\ri0\f1\fs32\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\b The Clef Inspector\b0   \par
