\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0\f1\b0\i0\fs24 D\f1 o Transposition\f0\f0 :\f0   If checked, then when \f1\f1\b0\i0 S\f1 ET\f0\f0  \f0 is pressed, transpose the music following the clef (as far as the next clef) on the staff and system on which the clef appears.  It is also possible to specify an additional transposition by octave (upper or lower) with the popup menu.\f0 \par
